<p itemprop="description">A lead data governance manager defines the strategic direction for data governance across the organisation and industry. They establish governance as a core organisational capability, influence policy development, and drive transformation in data management practices.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define strategic vision and roadmap for organisational data governance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish data governance as a core organisational capability and competency</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Influence industry standards and best practices in data governance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisational transformation in data management and stewardship</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build strategic partnerships with regulatory bodies and industry organisations</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop next-generation data governance frameworks and methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Advise executive leadership on data governance strategy and risk management</li>
    </ul>
</section>

